==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taenioglossa
<hw>Tae`ni*o*glos"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>taini`a</grk> a ribbon + <grk>glw^ssa</grk> a
tongue.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive division of
gastropod mollusks in which the odontophore is long and narrow, and
usually bears seven rows of teeth. It includes a large number of
families both marine and fresh-water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Taenioglossate</ent>⟦br⟧
